Text: This week i began working on the retrieval of the Geocode from addresss inputs, the function has yet to be fully implemented due to some hiccups along the way.
Due to the many ways of implementing a geocoder i sampled multiple ways.
Initially I tried to call on the API for nominatim, however I was unable to retrieve a Json file from the API call.

The reasoning for this was unclear to me however i could pinpoint some hypothetical reasons, one was the guidelines set by Nominatim where it required specific user agents to grant access for that connection.
Another hypothesis was the use of a local server.
Teacher2 then provided our group with a list of Geocoders, I tried out Geocoder PHP and had some difficulties making it work.
The main issue being the use of composer, as well as the specific documentation dependent on the User agent and Geocode provider.
But this didn't really matter since i couldn't get the package downloaded and working anyway (the initial step).

During our meeting with Eric he also made clear that the satellite function was a necessity in the soil industry, so we would likely have our code converted from leaflet to Google maps during the handover.
So for functionality sakes we will be temporarily using Koko's account to request for Googe Geocode information.
Now was the issue with implementing this code into the current code that Bibi had in place already.
Since we are hoping to have users search based on Latitude and longitude as well as address many things in the current code had to be changed.
As currently the code takes the current input and directly puts it into Roros API without filtering via regex.
This included many of the front end functionalities such as the serach radius circle and updating search circle etc.
I will be hopefully dealing with this today with Bibi.
